=== scene_3_initial_approach ===
Rain taps against {player_name}'s apartment windows, the gentle rhythm a counterpoint to {player_pronoun_possessive} racing thoughts. {player_pronoun_possessive} small living space has transformed over the past weeks—walls now covered with maps of Nexus City marked with {player_pronoun_possessive} notations, shelves lined with journals filled with observations the official systems refuse to acknowledge, and a modified spectral visor {player_pronoun_subject} has adjusted to capture what standard equipment cannot.

The scent of herbal tea mingles with the sharp tang of magical reagents {player_pronoun_subject} has been using to test theories. {player_pronoun_possessive} fingers are stained with the blue-black ink of {player_pronoun_possessive} documentation pen, and {player_pronoun_possessive} eyes burn from too many late nights poring over historical texts borrowed from the Antiquarian Archive.

On {player_pronoun_possessive} desk, the unmarked data chip Mira slipped {player_pronoun_object} projects a holographic overlay of the city, pinpointing locations where others have documented similar anomalies. The patterns are too consistent, too structured to be mere residue or coincidence. They form a network—ancient, deliberate, and hidden in plain sight.

{player_pronoun_possessive} official {player_title}'s medallion lies beside the projection, its polished surface reflecting the dancing lights. The oath {player_pronoun_subject} took when receiving it echoes in {player_pronoun_possessive} memory: "To document all magic, to preserve knowledge, to maintain the order established after the Awakening."

But what if that order was built on incomplete information—or worse, deliberate deception?

Elias's careful evasion, Mira's furtive alliance, the system's programmed dismissal of evidence—all point to a conspiracy of silence surrounding these ancient patterns. A conspiracy that extends to the highest levels of the Concordat.

{player_name} runs {player_pronoun_possessive} fingers over a fragment of stone {player_pronoun_subject} collected from near one of the patterns—a small piece that broke off naturally, not taken deliberately. Even this tiny fragment pulses with a subtle energy unlike anything in the standardized magical spectrum.

The rain intensifies, drumming against the glass as {player_pronoun_subject} considers {player_pronoun_possessive} next steps. This discovery is too significant to ignore, but pursuing it means risking everything—{player_pronoun_possessive} position, {player_pronoun_possessive} reputation, possibly more. The anomalous patterns have become a map to a hidden truth, one that challenges the very foundations of modern magical understanding.

How will {player_name} proceed?

